The paper deals with the problem of drawing trees with perfect angular resolution, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the area requirements for these drawings, which is related to graph drawing (cs.GR) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of Lombardi-style drawings is also mentioned, which is a technique commonly used in information visualization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the properties of trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
